  "answer": "## Evidence\nحديث (اختلاف أمتي رحمة) هو حديث موضوع، حيث قال ابن حزم: \"هذا من أفسد قول يكون، لأنه لو كان الاختلاف رحمة لكان الاتفاق سخطاً\". وأكد الألباني أنه لا أصل له، وذكر السبكي أنه لم يقف له على سند صحيح ولا ضعيف ولا موضوع. لذلك، يُعتبر هذا الحديث ضعيفاً جداً ولا يُعتمد عليه في الأمور الشرعية.\n\n## Evidence Translation\n> The hadith (The disagreement of my Ummah is a mercy) is a fabricated hadith. Ibn Hazm said: \"This is one of the most corrupt statements, for if disagreement were a mercy, then agreement would be a wrath.\" Al-Albani confirmed that it has no basis, and Al-Subki mentioned that he found no authentic, weak, or fabricated chain for it. Therefore, this hadith is considered very weak and is not relied upon in legal matters.\n\n## Explanation\nThe hadith in question, which claims that the disagreement among the Muslim community is a form of mercy, has been thoroughly critiqued by scholars. Ibn Hazm categorically rejected it, arguing that if disagreement were indeed a mercy, then consensus would be viewed as a form of divine displeasure. Al-Albani and Al-Subki further supported this view by stating that there is no authentic chain of narration for this hadith, rendering it unreliable for legal rulings. Thus, it is important for scholars and followers alike to be cautious about relying on such narrations in matters of Islamic jurisprudence.\n\n## Source\n1. ابن حزم، \"الفصل في الملل والنحل\".\n2. الألباني، \"سلسلة الأحاديث الضعيفة\".\n3. السبكي، \"طبقات الشافعية\".",
